y:inline-block;margin-bottom:3px;"><b>Role : </b></label> <span style="display:inline-block;width:500px">Site Reliability Engineer</span> </div>  </div> </div> <div style="margin-bottom:30px;">  <div style="font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:10px;color:#F79647;">WORK EXPERIENCE</div>  <div style="margin-bottom:15px;"> <div style="margin-bottom:3px;">  <span style="font-weight:bold;">SRE Technical lead</span>   <span style="color:#A6A6A5;">Jan '26 - May '26</span>  </div>  <div style="color:#4E81BD;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:3px;">VXI Global Solutions LLC</div>   Key Responsibilities & Achievements:
o	Led end-to-end observability transformation by migrating from SolarWinds to a scalable GCP + Grafana platform, significantly improving monitoring coverage and reducing alert noise.
o	Architected and implemented centralized observability across infrastructure, network, and application layers using GCP Monitoring, MQL, Grafana, and BindPlane.
o	Designed and optimized alerting strategies, improving incident detection accuracy and reducing mean time to detect (MTTD) and resolve (MTTR).
o	Defined and enforced SRE best practices including SLI/SLO frameworks, error budgets, and blameless postmortems to improve service reliability and accountability.
o	Built high-performance, actionable dashboards for large-scale environments, enabling faster decision-making and proactive issue identification.
o	Automated monitoring configurations, health checks, and operational workflows using scripting and infrastructure automation tools, reducing manual intervention and operational toil.
o	Led incident response for critical production issues, performing deep RCA and implementing preventive measures to enhance system stability.
o	Performed root cause analysis (RCA) for critical infrastructure and network incidents, identifying recurring issues and implementing preventive corrective actions. 
o	Managed end-to-end incident response and troubleshooting for production outages affecting network connectivity, server availability, and enterprise applications.
o	Established and maintained runbooks, SOPs, escalation procedures, and knowledge documentation for efficient incident management and operational consistency.
o	Monitored infrastructure utilization, bandwidth trends, device health, and system performance to support capacity planning and proactive maintenance activities.
o	Collaborated with network, infrastructure, cloud, and application teams to enhance system observability, reliability, scalability, and operational resilience.
o	Established runbooks and standard operating procedures (SOPs) for high-availability systems, improving response consistency and reducing resolution time.
o	Integrated telemetry pipelines using BindPlane to enable seamless data collection and visualization across distributed systems.
o	Collaborated with development and infrastructure teams to embed reliability, observability, and scalability into system design.
o	Ensured adherence to ITIL practices including Incident, Problem, and Change Management to maintain service quality and compliance.  </div>  <div style="margin-bottom:15px;"> <div style="margin-bottom:3px;">  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Senior Technical Lead</span>   <span style="color:#A6A6A5;">Sep '24 - Jan '26</span>  </div>  <div style="color:#4E81BD;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:3px;">HCLTech</div>   Key Responsibilities & Achievements:
